This indicates an overtaking maneuver or a shift in leading position. Thus, frame 1 must temporally precede frame 0.

Combining these observations, the most logical sequence tells a story of the red and white cyclist catching up and overtaking the other rider. The frames showing the red and white cyclist in action (2, 3, 4) would naturally occur during the effort of closing the gap or maintaining speed to complete the overtake. Therefore, the sequence begins with the red and white cyclist behind (frame 1), then shows their pedaling effort (frames 2, 3, 4), and concludes with them alongside or ahead (frame 0).
